query: Which singles went straight to number one on the French Singles Chart? Summarize the basic information of these singles.
summary: In 1991,"You Rock My World" and "Hips Don'T Lie 1" by Michael Jackson, "When The Rain Begins To Fall" by Jermaine Jackson and "Don't Let The Sun Go Down On Me" by Elton John all reached number one on the French Singles Chart. Michael Jackson's single, "You Rock My World," went straight to the number one spot, staying for two weeks at this position. "Hips Don't Lie 1" also stayed for just two weeks at the top spot.

query: How many Grand Slam titles did Katarina Srebotnik win? Summarize the basic information of these titles.
summary: Katarina Srebotnik won five Grand Slam titles in total: 1999 French Open, 2003 US Open, 2006 French Open, 2010 French Open and 2011 Australian Open. She won the 1999 French Open with partner Piet Norval against Larisa Neiland Rick Leach (6-3, 3-6, 6-3), the 2003 US Open with partner Bob Bryan against Lina Krasnoroutskaya Daniel Nestor (5-7, 7-5, 7-6(7-5)), the 2006 French Open with partner Nenad Zimonjić against Elena Likhovtseva Daniel Nestor (6-3, 6-4), 2010 French Open with partner Nenad Zimonjić against Yaroslava Shvedova Julian Knowle (4-6, 7-6(7-5), and 2011 Australian Open with partner Daniel Nestor against Yung - Jan Chan Paul Hanley (6–3 3–6 [10–7]).

query: In which season San Diego Gulls played best, and why?
summary: The San Diego Gulls played best in the 2003-04 season. This season had the highest winning percentage of all the seasons listed at 0.75. Additionally, the Gulls had the lowest number of penalty minutes at 1594 and the second lowest goals against at 177.
